BFN 

  [Text] Tallinn, Mar 27, BNS -- Estonia exported 1,294.0 
million kroons worth of goods and commodities in April, a report 
based on customs statistics shows. Imports for the same month 
were reported at 1,726.8 million kroons. 
  Imports exceeded exports by 432.3 million kroons, but the 
overall foreign trade deficit declined 71.4 million kroons when 
compared with the preceding month. The decline in total exports 
in one month was 91.3 million kroons, against a 161.6 million 
kroon decline in imports. 
  Temporary exports of goods due to be re-imported made up 1.6 
percent, and re-export, 21.8 percent of the total exports. 
Temporary imports made up 18.9 percent, and re-imports, 0.93 
percent of total imports. Estonia also received 21.4 million 
kroons worth of goods in humanitarian aid, slightly down from 
the respective figure of 23.8 million in March. Humanitarian 
aid accounted for 1.2 percent of the imports in April and for 
1.3 percent in March. 
  Estonia traded with 79 countries, out of whom the country 
reported a postitive trade balance with 31. 
  The leading foreign trade partners and their share in the 
total sales in April were as follows (figures for March in 
parentheses): 


